sequenceDiagram
    actor User as Guest
    participant fe@{ "type": "boundary" } as Frontend
    participant API@{ "type": "control" } as API
    participant svc@{ "type": "control" } as ReviewService
    participant cld@{ "type": "boundary" } as Cloudinary
    participant db@{ "type": "database" } as Database

    Note over User,db: Submit a review after a COMPLETED booking

    User->>+fe: Open completed booking → "Leave review"
    fe->>+API: POST /review (bookingId, roomId, rating, comment, images[])
    API->>API: verifyToken + checkBanned
    API->>API: Validate body (CreateReviewSchema)

    alt Validation failed
        API-->>fe: 400 ValidationError
        fe-->>User: Show field errors
    else Validation passed
        API->>+db: booking.findUnique(id = bookingId)
        db-->>-API: booking or null

        alt Booking not COMPLETED (or not found)
            API-->>fe: 403 "You can only review after finish your booking"
            fe-->>User: Show error
        else Booking is COMPLETED
            API->>+svc: handleCreateReview(userId, body)
            svc->>+db: booking.findUnique(id) (re-check inside service)
            db-->>-svc: booking

            alt Booking missing
                svc-->>API: NotFoundError
            else booking.userId !== current user
                svc-->>API: ForbiddenError "This booking does not belong to you."
            else booking.roomId !== submitted roomId
                svc-->>API: BadRequestError "Room does not match booking."
            else All checks pass
                loop For each image (parallel)
                    svc->>+cld: upload(img)
                    cld-->>-svc: { image_url, public_id }
                end

                svc->>+db: review.create(<br/>userId, roomId, bookingId,<br/>rating, comment, images.create=[...])
                alt DB create failed
                    db-->>svc: Error
                    svc->>cld: destroy(public_id) for each uploaded image
                    svc-->>API: Throw
                else DB create ok
                    db-->>-svc: review (with images)
                    svc-->>-API: review
                    API-->>fe: 200 "Review created successfully"
                    fe-->>-User: Show review on room page
                end
            end
        end
    end

    Note over User,db: GET /review/:roomId is public (no auth).<br/>PUT/DELETE /review/:reviewId require owner or ADMIN.
